message: "If you use claude-consensus in research or software, please cite it as below."
title: "claude-consensus: a multi-machine consensus protocol for AI agents"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Dziatkovskii
    given-names: Anton
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7408-3054"
    affiliation: "Palo Alto AI Research Lab"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Palo-Alto-AI-Research-Lab/claude-consensus"
url: "https://github.com/Palo-Alto-AI-Research-Lab/claude-consensus"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - multi-agent systems
  - consensus protocol
  - AI agents
  - distributed systems
  - homeostatics
  - cybernetics
abstract: >-
  Run AI agents across machines without state drift: consensus protocol
  (propose/counter/accept/commit), dual-rail message bus, ACK discipline,
  self-healing sync. The protocol's three-circuit safety design (steady-state,
  adaptive, protective) follows the homeostatic-governance model developed in
  the author's research on homeostatic principles in decentralized systems.
